Evanson Asset Management LLC Sells 131 Shares of Procter & Gamble Company (The) (NYSE:PG)


					Posted by Harper Lund on Jul 21st, 2017 // No Comments




Evanson Asset Management LLC cut its position in  Procter & Gamble Company (The) (NYSE:PG) by 1.9% during the first quarter, according to its most recent 13F filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The fund owned 6,835 shares of the company’s stock after selling 131 shares during the period. Evanson Asset Management LLC’s holdings in Procter & Gamble Company (The) were worth $614,000 as of its most recent filing with the SEC. 
Several other hedge funds have also recently bought and sold shares of PG. Norges Bank acquired a new position in shares of  Procter & Gamble Company (The) during the fourth quarter worth $1,918,188,000.  Asset Management One Co. Ltd. increased its position in shares of  Procter & Gamble Company (The) by 775.6% in the fourth quarter. Asset Management One Co. Ltd. now owns 4,562,545 shares of the company’s stock worth $383,723,000 after buying an additional 4,041,486 shares in the last quarter.  DZ BANK AG Deutsche Zentral Genossenschafts Bank Frankfurt am Main purchased a new stake in  Procter & Gamble Company (The) during the fourth quarter worth about $127,893,000.  Equity Investment Corp Acquisition Inc purchased a new stake in  Procter & Gamble Company (The) during the fourth quarter worth about $105,370,000.  Finally, State Street Corp boosted its stake in  Procter & Gamble Company (The) by 0.9% in the fourth quarter. State Street Corp now owns 117,814,233 shares of the company’s stock worth $9,905,824,000 after buying an additional 1,102,516 shares during the last quarter. 59.81% of the stock is currently owned by institutional investors. 


 Get Procter & Gamble Company (The) alerts:



Procter & Gamble Company (NYSE PG) traded down 0.119% during mid-day trading on Friday, hitting $88.495. 4,669,861 shares of the company were exchanged. The company’s 50-day moving average is $88.25 and its 200 day moving average is $88.33. The company has a market capitalization of $226.34 billion, a P/E ratio of 16.270 and a beta of 0.68. Procter & Gamble Company has a 12-month low of $81.18 and a 12-month high of $92.00.  Procter & Gamble Company (The) also saw unusually large options trading activity on Tuesday. Stock investors bought  17,404 call options on the company. This represents an increase of approximately 369% compared to the average volume of 3,714 call options.





Procter & Gamble Company (The) (NYSE:PG) last issued its quarterly earnings results on Wednesday, April 26th. The company reported $0.96 EPS for the quarter, topping analysts’ consensus estimates of $0.94 by $0.02. The company had revenue of $15.61 billion for the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $15.70 billion. Procter & Gamble Company (The) had a net margin of 23.14% and a return on equity of 19.30%. Procter & Gamble Company (The)’s revenue was down 1.0% compared to the same quarter last year. During the same quarter in the previous year, the business earned $0.86 earnings per share.  Analysts expect that  Procter & Gamble Company will post $3.85 EPS for the current year. 
The company also recently announced a quarterly dividend, which will be paid on Tuesday, August 15th. Investors of record on Friday, July 21st will be issued a $0.6896 dividend. The ex-dividend date of this dividend is Wednesday, July 19th. This represents a $2.76 annualized dividend and a yield of 3.11%. Procter & Gamble Company (The)’s payout ratio is 50.55%. 
ILLEGAL ACTIVITY NOTICE: This story was first  posted by Chaffey Breeze and is owned by of Chaffey Breeze. If you are accessing this story on another domain, it was copied illegally and reposted in violation of US and international copyright and trademark laws. The correct version of this story can be accessed at https://www.chaffeybreeze.com/2017/07/21/procter-gamble-company-the-pg-position-reduced-by-evanson-asset-management-llc-updated-updated-updated.html. 
Several research firms recently weighed in on PG. UBS AG  reissued a “buy” rating and set a $101.00 price objective on shares of Procter & Gamble Company (The) in a research report on Thursday, March 23rd. BidaskClub cut Procter & Gamble Company (The) from a “hold” rating to a “sell” rating in a research report on Wednesday, July 12th. Jefferies Group LLC  reissued a “buy” rating and set a $98.00 price objective on shares of Procter & Gamble Company (The) in a research report on Monday. Royal Bank Of Canada  restated a “hold” rating and set a $80.00 price target on shares of Procter & Gamble Company (The) in a research note on Friday, June 30th. Finally, Vetr lowered Procter & Gamble Company (The) from a “hold” rating to a “sell” rating and set a $83.75 price objective on the stock. in a research note on Monday, July 3rd. Four analysts have rated the stock with a sell rating, ten have given a hold rating and seven have given a buy rating to the company. The stock presently has an average rating of “Hold” and an average price target of $87.04.
In related news, insider Patrice Louvet sold 3,837 shares of the business’s stock in a transaction on Thursday, May 4th. The shares were sold at an average price of $87.00, for a total value of $333,819.00. Following the transaction, the insider now owns 46,913 shares in the company, valued at $4,081,431. The transaction was disclosed in a document filed with the SEC, which is available through this link. Also, insider Steven D. Bishop sold 2,668 shares of the business’s stock in a transaction on Monday, May 1st. The shares were sold at an average price of $87.34, for a total transaction of $233,023.12. Following the completion of the transaction, the insider now owns 43,608 shares in the company, valued at approximately $3,808,722.72. The disclosure for this sale can be found here. In the last 90 days, insiders sold 199,891 shares of company stock worth $17,276,637. 0.35% of the stock is owned by company insiders. 
Procter & Gamble Company (The) Company Profile
The Procter & Gamble Company is focused on providing branded consumer packaged goods to the consumers across the world. The Company operates through five segments: Beauty; Grooming; Health Care; Fabric & Home Care, and Baby, Feminine & Family Care. The Company sells its products in approximately 180 countries and territories primarily through mass merchandisers, grocery stores, membership club stores, drug stores, department stores, distributors, baby stores, specialty beauty stores, e-commerce, high-frequency stores and pharmacies.







