Evanson Asset Management Cut Microsoft (MSFT) Holding By $323,020, Open Text (OTEX) Shorts Increased By 4.37%

July 25, 2017 - By Peter Erickson

Evanson Asset Management Llc decreased Microsoft Corp (MSFT) stake by 20.81% reported in 2016Q4 SEC filing. Evanson Asset Management Llc sold 5,210 shares as Microsoft Corp (MSFT)’s stock rose 4.75%. The Evanson Asset Management Llc holds 19,827 shares with $1.23M value, down from 25,037 last quarter. Microsoft Corp now has $568.38 billion valuation. The stock rose 0.29% or $0.21 reaching $73.81. About 7.40 million shares traded. Microsoft Corporation (NASDAQ:MSFT) has risen 34.52% since July 25, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 17.82% the S&P500.
 Open Text Corporation (NASDAQ:OTEX) had an increase of 4.37% in short interest. OTEX’s SI was 7.48 million shares in July as released by FINRA. Its up 4.37% from 7.16 million shares previously. With 474,700 avg volume, 16 days are for Open Text Corporation (NASDAQ:OTEX)’s short sellers to cover OTEX’s short positions. The SI to Open Text Corporation’s float is 2.91%. About 75,995 shares traded. Open Text Corp (USA) (NASDAQ:OTEX) has risen 15.94% since July 25, 2016 and is uptrending. It has underperformed by 0.76% the S&P500.







Open Text Corporation provides a platform and suite of software services and products that assist organizations in finding, utilizing, and sharing business information from any device. The company has market cap of $8.83 billion. The Firm designs, develops, markets and sells Enterprise Information Management software and solutions. It has a 7.66 P/E ratio. The Company’s EIM offerings include Enterprise Content Management (ECM), Business Process Management (BPM), Customer Experience Management (CEM), Business Network, Discovery and Analytics.
